message.body: Hey! Are you around Friday evening, maybe for dinner?
Ooh I'd love to hang out, friday may not be the best bet though... What's your schedule like this weekend?
Yeah! The times we are not free are sat. lunch and sun. dinner...when are you around?

Cool, sat night would probably be best for me. What were you thinking? You guys are welcome to come over for dinner but I have to warn that my house is a little gross haha. Also, I hear Fairleigh is around?
Okay! Well she is just here for dinner tonight which is why I asked about today
Oh bummer, I'm already on my way to a potluck. Excited to see you tomorrow though
Yeah!
HOW MANY RADICAL FEMINISTS DOES IT TAKE TO SCREW IN A LIGHTBULB?
THAT'S NOT FUNNY
Bahahaha.
Wait read my foot is hilarious. And it wasnt offensive! Someone at my UU potluck told that joke and I thought to myself "that's not funny" and then it was the punch line. Ahahaha
Your mom is offensive. And YESS observing people's awkward dates is my favorite.
That yes was not supposed to be capitalized it was autocorrect in not that enthusiastic about it. Also I'm 2 beers in and actually drunk this is a little pathetic
Hey there!
Zinaaaa

Hey sorry I stopped by work this morning, just seeing text. I am about to go on a hike in rock creek park but we shouldn't be too long, so pretty much free any time. And I could do either restaurant or at my house, my only request would be a not super expensive restaurant
Sounds good, we are busy before dinner so do you know what time you might want to do dinner?
Do you just want to text me when you're free? Also, is it okay if I invite some friends along?
Sure and sure!
Around what time do you think you'll be back?
We are shooting for getting to you around 6:30. What is your address? Also does that timing work?
Actually probably between 6:30 and 7

Yup that's good. And I am hanging out at le pain quotidien in downtown Bethesda, but I can meet you anywhere near the metro. Does Anna have any restaurant suggestions? She probably knows the area better than I do.
She suggests cosi...pricewise it's like panera. What do you think? There's also a Mexican place called Rio Grande that's sit down but not ridiculously $$ and we can share dishes. There's also Indian.
Indian sounds good. Which place?
Haandi
Also we are running a little behind so we will be there in about half an hour...do you want to meet at the restaurant?
Ok cool. I live right there so we will prob wait at mine. Text me when you are like 5-10 min away and Â we will walk over.
Okay! We are 22 min. now and ill text again
Ok so I did not text but we are close!
Aka looking for parking
Ok on our way but you may beat us there, go ahead and get a table for 5 if you do
Sounds good
